The touch controls are a bit clunky, but get the job done. I used to enjoy this game, but the need for jewels to achieve story progression (buying dishes and items that help greatly in exploration) has taken away quite a bit of that enjoyment. If you can not move up in leagues, you continue to wander the same maps forever, live off of selling the random daikon and flour that you can spare to Fred while only getting by selling eggs on the menu, and struggling to purchase things to help your store, as well as your adventuring. I also had to request a refund for the jewels, as the app crashed almost instantly after making a purchase and the jewels were never added to my inventory (even though my bank listed the charge and Google sent me a purchase confirmation email). I attempted to contact the developer, but no dice.

This would easily be one of the best RPGs on Android if it weren't for a few very annoying UI bugs.  The combat reminds me of Grandia, which is great.  Gameplay involves using the menu quite a bit, but resets everytime you do anything. This means that something trivial like making some food takes far longer and far more clicks than it should.  The game has no auto-save and is prone to crashing, which means your very likely to lose your progress (and your jewel purchases).  Its a pay game, but still has in-app purchases.   Each of these issues to me is 1 star off the rating.

Love it worth every dime.....have to be honest though not happy having too pay twice for the game but its worth the inital charge......glad you dont have too by gems just too play there could be better value packs for them though....would love too see more games by you guys this was really well done and really fun........please make more games like this.... My only issue thus far is how difficult it seems to progress the story along

Adventure Bar Story delivers a unique experience and  addicting gameplay! No problems running on my Htc Evo 4g (original) . If you are an rpg fan looking for something exciting and different brought to the field, download ABS and you won't be disappointed. Recommend running the Lite Version before you buy to see if device is compatible.
I bought the app through the game and had to have google refund it because it still said i have to pay and no install button. had to repay and everything only using google play.

I would rather fill my time wasting app space with rpgs than anything else, any day. This game is great fun, very addicting.  The characters are cute and quirky and any completionist will go nuts trying to find all the food combos. It takes a good 10 game days before you will really understand how the game works.  Some aspects are not explained outright but become more apparent as you go (such as new areas unlocking, food contest participation).

Game itself is quite fun and really cute. I feel it's held back a bit by a terrible menu system that is riddled with graphical errors. Sliders disappear until released, sell menu, menus for food - all invisible. Would rate higher but in a game where 50% is a sim it really holds it back..

I've seen more expensive games, and it's not like this game NEEDS you to buy jewels. I do agree that it was a bit confusing, though, to have to unlock the full story by buying the game. Also, their BGM is amazing.
Love the game. If you play the lite version, you'll know if you'll want the rest. E-mailed them about importing my save file from lite to full, got a no ten days later. A bargain at $2 though.
Love it, it's so fun and once you get the hang of things you can really succeed at the game. Worth the money :)

Cleverly combines full fledged rpg and restaurant cooking management genres into one tight package. I definitely recommend this one. Try the free one first though...just in case. Small note...it still has in app purchases, so that really sucks.
A 1star until bug is resolved

Good game. some FC issues. There should be a way to migrate data from the demo (LITE) to the full game upon purchase. but maybe that would be impossible without more permissions? I really really appreciate that this app doesn't demand tons of ridiculous permissions like so many other games on here do.
Crashed when using sword dance
Awesome game

Game is pretty decent. In app purchases detract a little bit but are not needed to play the game at all. On my galaxy 10.1 when I go to sell something the menu disappears from sight but it's still there because if I press where the sell button is it'll make the sale.
First, the game is easy n fun to play. Second, it works well on my phone, plus is easy on my batteries. So it's top in my Books
Good game good idea I don't like the double dipping if I bought this game than I shouldn't need jewels to buy rare stuff I should be able to find it
Very worth the price for the full game.
Runs great,  its innovative without being overcomplicated,  fun and easy to get into,  I'm greatly impressed
Has the potential to be great but annoying random force closing (LgP920) and in app greed after paying for the game makes it hard to recommend.
